    private int age;      // Private field
```

- **`private`**: These fields can only be accessed within the `Person` class itself. This is data hiding - a core OOP principle.

## Getter and Setter Methods

```java
public void setName(String name) {
    this.name = name;
}

public String getName() {
    return name;
}

public void setAge(int age) {
    this.age = age;
}

public int getAge() {
    return age;
}
```

- **Setters** (`setName`, `setAge`): Allow you to assign values to the private fields
- **Getters** (`getName`, `getAge`): Allow you to retrieve values from the private fields
- **`this`**: Refers to the current object instance

