```java
import java.io.BufferedReader;
import java.io.FileReader;
import java.io.IOException;

public class FileReaderExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        try (BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new FileReader("example.txt"))) {
            String line;
            while ((line = br.readLine()) != null) {
                System.out.println(line);
            }
        } catch (IOException e) {
            System.out.println("Error reading file: " + e.getMessage());
        }
    }
}
```

This program uses try-with-resources to ensure the `BufferedReader` is closed properly, even if an exception occurs. It reads lines from a file and prints them to the console, handling any IO exceptions that might arise.

